<li>20,000mAh is a good bit of charge for your devices</li>
<li>Each one has 3 USB ports (2 USB-A and 1 USB-C)</li>
<li>63 Watts total (45W USB-C + 18W USB-A)</li>
<li>Each comes with a USB-C cable and a USB-A to USB-C adapter</li>
<li>Are they available in Georgia Red: Nope, just a sort of weirdly textured looking dark gray/black</li>
</ul><h1>When You Need It</h1><p>To: Terrance D. Hell<br />
From: Georgio Decker<br />
Subject: RE: The Alpine Vista Killer, complete manuscript</p>
<p>Terry!</p>
<p>I read your newest novel draft eagerly over the weekend, and I will say, for the first third, it seemed like another chilling Terrance D. Hell masterpiece.</p>
<p>A slasher? At a ski resort? With all roads out closed due to an avalanche? What a fantastic premise!</p>
<p>But I couldn’t help but feel let down by the final two-thirds. Specifically, there was a scene in chapter seven where Gregory, a gondola attendant, observes the killer take off his ski mask. He goes to text for help, but finds his phone dead. A perfect setup for another scene of grisly delight! Only, Gregory merely takes out an Einova 63W 20,000mAh Power Bank (very specific branding to include, I might add), charges his phone enough to get power, and texts the ski patrol. They then show up and apprehend the criminal, leaving another 200 pages of the book, which you fill by simply describing people skiing happily.</p>
<p>I was wondering if you might want to rethink this plot point to maximize the terror?</p>
<p>Let me know if you have any questions!</p>
<p>Best,<br />
Georgio Decker<br />
Senior Editor<br />
Death Bells Publishing</p>
<hr />
<p>To:  Georgio Decker<br />
From: Terrance D. Hell<br />
Subject: RE: The Alpine Vista Killer, complete manuscript</p>
<p>It’s a matter of realism, Georgio. You can get a two-pack of those things for $30 these days. If someone’s phone just dies, a modern reader is going to be dubious.</p>
<p>TDH</p>
<hr />
<p>To: Terrance D. Hell<br />
From: Georgio Decker<br />
Subject: RE: The Alpine Vista Killer, complete manuscript</p>
<p>An interesting point, Terry! And far be it from me to tell a genius like you how to write your book!</p>
<p>But, what if, hear me out: he drops the power bank and it breaks? Wouldn’t that add some more tension?</p>
<p>Just something to chew on.</p>
<p>Best,<br />
Georgio Decker<br />
Senior Editor<br />
Death Bells Publishing</p>
<hr />
<p>To:  Georgio Decker<br />
From: Terrance D. Hell<br />
Subject: RE: The Alpine Vista Killer, complete manuscript</p>
<p>Great idea, Georgio. Updated manuscript attached.</p>
<p>TDH</p>
